In article <1994May8.031854.10778@solaris.rz.tu-clausthal.de> czeranski@rz.tu-clausthal.de (Joerg Czeranski) writes:
:Hello!
:
:I read that one of the last steps of breaking RSA-129 was to
:solve a large (ca. 600000x600000) sparse linear equation system.
:

The system is over Z/2Z.

:How was this done?  Is the source code for this step available?
 
Gaussian Elimination. 

Using techniques due to A. Odlyzko, the large sparse matrix was partially
reduced to one a lot smaller but a lot denser. This final dense matrix
was then solved on a MasPar in about 40 hours.

The final matrix was about 160K x 160K if memory serves.

